HEADWORD: Crashing
<hw>Crash"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The noise of many things falling
and breaking at once.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There shall be . . . a great <qex>crashing</qex> from the
hills.</q> <rj><qau>Zeph. i. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crasis</ent>⟦br⟧
